MALACAÑANG Manila

PROCLAMATION NO . 603

EXCLUDING FROM THE OPERATION OF PROCLAMATION NO. 420, DATED JULY 5, 1994, PROCLAMATION NO. 198, DATED JUNE 29, 1993 AND PROCLAMATION NO. 1907 DATED JANUARY 23, 1907, WHICH ESTABLISHED THE CAMP JOHN HAY MILITARY RESERVATION (NOW THE JOHN HAY ECONOMIC ZONE), A CERTAIN PARCEL EMBRACED THEREIN SITUATED AT LOAKAN ROAD, BAGUIO CITY, ISLAND OF LUZON AND FURTHER DESIGNATING THE SAME OFFICE AND BODEGA SITE OF THE NATIONAL FOOD AUTHORITY

Upon the recommendation of the Secretary of Environment and Natural Resources and pursuant to the authority vested in me by law, I, GLORIA MACAPAGAL-ARROYO , President of the Philippines, do hereby exclude from the operation of Proclamation No. 420 dated July 5, 1994, Proclamation No. 198 dated June 29, 1993 and Proclamation No. 1907 dated January 23, 1907, which established the Camp John Hay Military Reservation (now the John Hay Special Economic Zone), a certain parcel of the public domain situated in Loakan Road, Baguio City, Island of Luzon and further designating the same for office and bodega site purposes of the National Food Authority, subject to private rights, if there be any, which parcel of land is more particularly described as follows:

TECHNICAL DESCRIPTION Sgs-CAR-000072

A parcel of land Sgs-CAR-000072 situated at res. Sec “J”, Barangay Apugan, Loakan, Baguio City, Island of Luzon. Bounded on the W., along line 1-2 and SW., along line 2-3-4-5 by Loakan Road (30.00 m. wide)., on the N., along lines 5-6-7-8 Lot 15, Ccs-131102-000030 (Port)., on the E., along lines 8-9 by Lot 15, Ccs-131102-000030 (Port)., on the S., along lines 9-1 by EPZA. Beginning at the point marked “1” on the plan being N. 65 deg. 12′ E., 1089.06 m. from triangulation “BOYD” Baguio Townsite, thence;

28.53 m. to point 2;

99.80 m. to point 3;

59.47 m. to point 4;

109.19 m. to point 5;

46.08 m. to point 6;

14.16 m. to point 7;

162.84 m. to point 8;

183.04 m. to point 9;

25.01 m. to point of

beginning, containing an area of TWENTY ONE THOUSAND ONE HUNDRED FIFTEEN (21,115) square meters, more or less.

All point referred to are indicated on the plan and are marked on the ground as follows: Corners 6-7-8-9 by G.I. Pipe 2″ diameter and the rest by P.S. cyl. Conc. Mons. 15 x 40 cms: Bearings True. Date of segregation survey on March 15 and August 3, 2001 executed by Engineer Ramon P. Dawas and was approved on September 14, 2001.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF , I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

DONE in the City of Manila, this 13 th day of April, in the year of Our Lord, Two Thousand and Four.

(Sgd.) GLORIA MACAPAGAL-ARROYO

By the President: (Sgd.) ALBERTO G. ROMULO Executive Secretary

